29/05/2011
BERLIN, Germany -- Police announced on Friday (May 27th) that Greece's consulate in Berlin had been attacked with stones and paint bombs.
According to witnesses, about ten masked men attacked the building during the night, causing minor property damage.
German Foreign Minister Guido Westerwelle described the incident as "appalling" and phoned Greek counterpart Dimitris Droutsas to express his regret.
(Greek Reporter, Eleftherotypia, Ta Nea - 27/05/11)
